-- Nigeria's Stanbic IBTC to raise 30 bln naira Tier II capital
-- By Chijioke Ohuocha
-- Thu Aug 07, 2014 09:48AM EDT
-- None



LAGOS, Aug 7 (Reuters) - Stanbic IBTC <IBTC.LG>, the Nigerian unit of South Africa's Standard Bank <SBKJ.J>, plans to raise up to 30 billion naira in Tier II capital, a presentation on its website said on Thursday.

CEO Sola David-Borha confirmed the capital raise during an analysts conference call on Thursday but said the actual amount would depend on market conditions and regulatory guidelines. She did not provide a timeline.